23/12/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Parliament says the United States is pleased with the declaration, adopted three days ago, that supports in principle the relocation of US military bases to Bulgaria. Following a meeting between US Ambassador to Sofia James Pardew and Parliamentary Chairman Ognyan Gerdzhikov, parliament issued a press release Monday (22 December). It quoted Pardew as saying US experts would likely continue evaluating possible base locations in Southeast Europe in the first months of 2004. (Trud, 24 Chassa - 23/12/03; BTA, BNR, BNT - 22/12/03)
